CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 14, 1941, pg. 11, reads: "There is something new under the sun, at least, Eleather Clements in her Broad Street Shop has found it. She gave a manicure party for her patrons last Wednesday which was novel and successful... Top, right: Miss Clements gives Bell Parker and Electric manicure... - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Manicurists, including Eleathor Clements in foreground doing nails of Bell Parker, in Clements Beauty Salon, with Mary Tracy wearing eyeglasses and standing in background, East Liberty
